    <text id="B0696T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Waldo writes regarding the use of the Methodist Episcopal Church and the conflict
                    between the Methodist and Baptist congregations in Waynesboro over the church's
                    use as a non-denominational school.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    Bureau <abbr expan="Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands">RF and AL</abbr> 4th
                    <abbr expan="Division">Div</abbr> 9th <abbr expan="Sub District">Sub
                        Dist</abbr>
                    <name type="recipient"><abbr expan="Edward">Ed</abbr> Baldwin<lb/><abbr
                            expan="John">Jno</abbr> Crawford &amp;c - Trustees <abbr
                            expan="Methodist Episcopal">ME</abbr> Church (<abbr expan="colored"
                        >c</abbr>)<lb/>Waynesboro <abbr expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr>
                    </name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1868-11-02">November 2 /68</date>
                        <name type="place">Staunton, <abbr expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr></name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute/>
                </opener>

                <p>By direction of the <abbr expan="Assistant Commissioner">Asst Comr</abbr>
                    Richmond <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr> I most respectfully <del rend="none" hand="h1"/>
                    in the matter of the difficulties existing <unclear>between</unclear> the
                    Methodists and Baptists in regard to the use of the Church building at
                    Waynesboro <unclear>&amp;c</unclear>
                    <unclear>that the</unclear> grant of $150 was made by the Bureau toward its
                    Erection with the express understanding that the building was to be used as a
                    house of <hi rend="underline">worship</hi> by the <hi rend="underline">Methodist</hi>
                    <hi rend="underline">denomination</hi> and <hi rend="underline">as</hi> a <hi
                        rend="underline">schoolhouse</hi>
                    <hi rend="underline">for</hi>
                    <hi rend="underline">all</hi>
                    <hi rend="underline">children</hi>
                    <hi rend="underline">without</hi>
                    <hi rend="underline">distinction</hi> of <hi rend="underline">sect.</hi> It is
                    expected <unclear>therefore</unclear> that the Methodists will do themselves no
                    discredit and their people no harm by trying to make the school in any way
                    denominational. It is further hoped and expected that both denominations will
                    unite in harmony in the use of said building for school purposes and that no
                    further difficulty may arise regarding it.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Very respectfully<lb/>Your obedient servant</salute>
                    <signed>Roswell Waldo<lb/><abbr expan="Assistant Sub Assistant Commissioner"
                            >A.S.A. Comr</abbr></signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
